postcontent: For sale is a rare and rarely used Loggy Bayou Monarch XL Prostaff hang-on tree stand. This is one of the lightest (if not lightest) tree stands of it's size (platform is 20x36) ever manufactured. It weighs literally just 10.0 lbs. Lone Wolf only dreams they could make and sell a stand of this size that is this light. I bought it several years ago to use when I took my kids out to hunt with me. I would go up a single person ladder and then quickly attach this stand, step onto it, and have my kids come up and sit next to me on the ladder stand. It worked like a charm but my kids are now big enough to use climbers themselves so I do not use this stand even once per year anymore. It has never been left out, just carried in and carried out three to four times. It's aluminum and the seat is very thickly padded and extremely comfortable. It hangs quickly with a 2" top strap and then a ratchet on the bottom to tightly seat the toothed V-notch base to the tree. This is an incredibly stable stand. It also has a foot rest and a waterproof seat cover which is built into a zippered pocket on the front of the seat. The stand is completely camoflauged. If you want a very light, very stable, very comfortable hang on, then I defy you to find anything being manufactured today that is it's equal within $100 of this price.  You are more than welcome to come see it and we can carry it out to a tree in my yard so you can see just how quickly it installs and how immensely comfortable it is. Call Steve at REDACTED. postcontent:
These triggers were just released at SHOT show a few weeks back and have been a huge hit ever since. I have included the manufacturer's comment below. But at its most basic this is a way to have an excellent rapid fire AR, capable of up to 700 round per minute, which is faster than some full-auto rifle cyclic rates. But at the same time you don't sacrifice any functionality in your rifle with ugly boxy stocks or rapid-fire only triggers. This will complete an AR build, to give you the best all around gun possible. In the patented 3rd position it uses the BCG recoil to give the shortest reset available on the market, allowing the trigger to be manipulated much faster than anything else. But left in normal semi-auto mode it has a 4.5 lb match-grade trigger that has been directly compared to Timney and Geissele units. These units are MAP priced at $495, which means we aren't allowed to advertise and sale them for any cheaper. However we are doing some special preorder deals on these, including free shipping or installation, among other things. Also ordering through us will not only be cheaper than buying online, the wait time will be much less. We can also build you an entire rifle with this trigger included. Contact us today for more information and to get on our initial order to ensure the special intro pricing offers. We are a FFL licensed dealer located in Stanfield, NC. 

From the Manufacturer - "The 3MR is a drop-in 3-mode fire control system with Safe, Semi-Automatic, and Tac-Con™’s patented 3rd Mode. The 3rd mode has a positive reset that dramatically reduces the split times between shots. The positive reset characteristic is achieved by transferring the force from the bolt carrier through the trigger assembly to assist the trigger back onto the front sear. As a result, this gives the firearm the fastest reset possible. Both semi and 3rd mode positions exhibit a non-adjustable 4.5 pound trigger pull weight."

title: For Sale:  Custom IWB Kydex Holster for the Walther PK380
postcontent:
This listing is for a very comfortable, and concealable Left Handed IWB custom Kydex holster for the Walther PK380. 

We at SSXHolsters take the following steps in creating each holster: 
First, we thermo-form our high quality 060 Kydex to the maximum pliability gradually, and without scorching the material with direct advice from the plastics industry leaders.    
Second, we hand press each holster up to 1200 lbs. psi. 
Third, we mill the holsters into the models shape/design, machine buff, then wet sand all edges to a nice smooth matte finish. 
All IWB holsters are fitted with a high quality metal belt clip attached at a single point with quality hardware and Loctite to provide a permanent bond while being forgiving of various body positions increasing comfort and ultimately more good people legally carrying their firearms on an everyday basis.  

Don't waste your money on the rest, spent it on the best!  

If there is ever an issue with your holster simply contact us with the information we provide with each shipment and we will either inform you how to address the issue easily, or we will fix it for you. We ask only that you pay return shipping. 

Why Kydex as opposed to other holster materials? 

Kydex®

KYDEX® (ACRYLIC/PVC ALLOY) SHEET

KYDEX® sheet is an extremely durable acrylic/PVC alloy extruded in a range of colors, patterns, textures, thicknesses, and grades to optimize long-term performance, appearance, and cost effectiveness across demanding and diverse end-use applications. Specialized grades of KYDEX® sheet are offered to satisfy requirements specific to thermoforming, membrane pressing, post-forming, brake-forming, and laminating, and to fit a broad range of specialized applications ranging from medical equipment housings and aircraft tray tables to retail store fixtures and trade show displays.

IMPACT RESISTANCE
No other thermoplastic sheet stands up to impact, and gouging like KYDEX® sheet. Depending on grade, KYDEX® sheet offers Notched Izod impact resistance to 18 ft-lbs/in., and is available in thicknesses from .028 to .500 inch to withstand levels of abuse from moderate to extreme. Due to its high degree of toughness and resilience, KYDEX® sheet can also be stretched at room temperature to twice its original dimension without breaking.



FLAME RETARDANCY
Depending on grade, KYDEX® sheet is available with fire ratings of UL Std. 94 V-0, UL Std. 94 5V; FAR 25.853 (a) and (d); FSTratings: ABD6031 D6-51377:FMVSS 302; Class I/A and others as described in the following pages.











CHEMICAL RESISTANCE
From sulfuric acid to brake fluid to carbon tetrachloride, high performance grades of KYDEX® sheet acrylic/PVC alloys are more resistant to a wider range of concentrated chemicals than any other thermoplastic. In fact, KYDEX® sheet meets the highest standards of chemical resistance for thermoplastic materials as defined inASTM D-1784 standard for Class 12454-C rigid polyvinyl chloride.



DIMENSIONAL STABILITY
Low water absorption and a relatively low coefficient of thermal expansion give parts made with KYDEX® sheet high dimensional stability.

CLEANABILITY
Tough stains, scuffs, and graffiti can be removed from KYDEX® surfaces using strong cleansers with no staining, fading, or surface damage.



DESIGN FREEDOM
KYDEX® sheet offers unprecedented design and manufacturing flexibility since:

Numerous grades are available to provide properties and certified ratings required for specialized applications.
An uncommonly wide variety of functional and aesthetic effects can be achieved since certain individual grades can be manufactured using a variety of techniques.
Many colors, patterns, textures, and thicknesses are common to grades intended for specific manufacturing methods allowing multicomponent end products to contain a wide variety of matching parts.

title: For Sale:  Custom IWB Kydex Holster for the Glock 17/19/22/23
postcontent:
This listing is for a very comfortable, and concealable Right Handed (Left hand draw is available) IWB custom Kydex holster for the Glock 17/19/22/23. 

We at SSXHolsters take the following steps in creating each holster: 
First, we thermo-form our high quality 060 Kydex to the maximum pliability without scorching the material with direct advice from the plastics industry leaders.    
Second, we hand press each holster up to 1200 lbs. psi. 
Third, we mill the holsters into the models shape/design, machine buff, then wet sand all edges to a nice smooth matte finish. 
All IWB holsters are fitted with high quality hardware.

Don't waste your money on the rest, spent it on the best!  

If there is ever an issue with your holster simply contact us with the information we provide with each shipment and we will either inform you how to address the issue easily, or we will fix it for you. We ask only that you pay return shipping. 

Why Kydex as opposed to other holster materials? 

Kydex®

KYDEX® (ACRYLIC/PVC ALLOY) SHEET

KYDEX® sheet is an extremely durable acrylic/PVC alloy extruded in a range of colors, patterns, textures, thicknesses, and grades to optimize long-term performance, appearance, and cost effectiveness across demanding and diverse end-use applications. Specialized grades of KYDEX® sheet are offered to satisfy requirements specific to thermoforming, membrane pressing, post-forming, brake-forming, and laminating, and to fit a broad range of specialized applications ranging from medical equipment housings and aircraft tray tables to retail store fixtures and trade show displays.

IMPACT RESISTANCE
No other thermoplastic sheet stands up to impact, and gouging like KYDEX® sheet. Depending on grade, KYDEX® sheet offers Notched Izod impact resistance to 18 ft-lbs/in., and is available in thicknesses from .028 to .500 inch to withstand levels of abuse from moderate to extreme. Due to its high degree of toughness and resilience, KYDEX® sheet can also be stretched at room temperature to twice its original dimension without breaking.



FLAME RETARDANCY
Depending on grade, KYDEX® sheet is available with fire ratings of UL Std. 94 V-0, UL Std. 94 5V; FAR 25.853 (a) and (d); FSTratings: ABD6031 D6-51377:FMVSS 302; Class I/A and others as described in the following pages.











CHEMICAL RESISTANCE
From sulfuric acid to brake fluid to carbon tetrachloride, high performance grades of KYDEX® sheet acrylic/PVC alloys are more resistant to a wider range of concentrated chemicals than any other thermoplastic. In fact, KYDEX® sheet meets the highest standards of chemical resistance for thermoplastic materials as defined inASTM D-1784 standard for Class 12454-C rigid polyvinyl chloride.



DIMENSIONAL STABILITY
Low water absorption and a relatively low coefficient of thermal expansion give parts made with KYDEX® sheet high dimensional stability.

CLEANABILITY
Tough stains, scuffs, and graffiti can be removed from KYDEX® surfaces using strong cleansers with no staining, fading, or surface damage.



DESIGN FREEDOM
KYDEX® sheet offers unprecedented design and manufacturing flexibility since:

Numerous grades are available to provide properties and certified ratings required for specialized applications.
An uncommonly wide variety of functional and aesthetic effects can be achieved since certain individual grades can be manufactured using a variety of techniques.
Many colors, patterns, textures, and thicknesses are common to grades intended for specific manufacturing methods allowing multicomponent end products to contain a wide variety of matching parts.

title: For Sale:  Polytech AK47
postcontent:
I promised myself I would never sell this rifle, however, I've got an opportunity to buy another dream gun, so this has to go to fund the purchase.  If you know AK47s then you know about the quality of the Polytech AK47 variants over just about any other variant out there.  If you don't, just google "Polytech AK Reviews" and you'll see they're considered to be the finest AK variants to end up in the US.  Anyway, take a look a the photos and I'll be glad to answer any questions you have.  These rifles are superior to the US rifles in that they were assembled in factories and shipped over here complete, not some random mix and match parts kit from Romania assembled by some idiot at Century Arms.  The factory this came from built and inspected the firearm before it was ever shipped.  As such, the finish and fitment is unlike anything you can buy on the market today.  I'm not the original owner as this was a KFS Atlanta import.  

Like all polytech AKs, this rifle has run flawlessly and has the smoothest bolt and action of any AK I've ever held.  I own an Arsenal SLR which is a fine firearm, but honestly, this one is just smoother shooting. This AK was made in the famed "Factory #386" where the Polytech Legends were produced.  When I take it to the range, it shoots 3-4MOA with iron sights and would likely do better if I was a better shot, haha.  Rifle comes with 2 30-round magazines and sling, I can add more magazines or ammo to the trade at additional expense, let me know what you're thinking.

title: For Sale/Trade:  M91/30 1934 hex izzy
postcontent:
Nagants in good enough shape to be salvaged were part of the soviets massive refurbishment program following ww2. The primary reasons behind the huge post war overhaul of large, obsolete rifle stockpiles were the anticipation of another impending world war, and the plan to call up seasoned veterans in defense of the motherland. Already familiar with their old mosin nagant rifles and revolvers, those veterans would likely have required very little new training and would easily and rapidly reintegrate into the red machine. 
With the development of newer semi auots that would have required extensive massive retraining, the important issue became of quick mobilization became apearant. However time passed and those great ww2 veterans eventually aged beyond the point of viability. While newer weapons took over the worlds battlefields, the stocks of long outdated ordnance were now imported to the USA. 

This is a pre war 1934 izzy manufacture m90/31 with hexagonal reciever with original russian laminate non refurbished stock. This rifles bore is stone mint shiny chromed out! "Have neer seen one like this" the weapon bears No refurbishment marks or other countrys arsenal markings! The metal has not a mark on it is stone mint! The magazine follower, action etc have no wear! Mint bore. All matching. No refurbishment marks from other countrys !!
This is a very early import that was sold wrapped in brown paper tied in twine. This rifle saw little to no action its entire life, maybe an officers or political gaurds weapon

The rifles antiquated lines, and historical signifigance is something to be sought after for years to come. This rifle was made well when an individuals workmanship was apreciated and one took pride in what they did. It also was a matter of national pride, a "we made it here" battle rifle.

title: For Sale:  REMINGTON 870 POLICE MAGNUM 12GA
postcontent:
Make: Remington 

Model: 870P Police Magnum

Caliber: 12 Guage

Location: Sacramento 

Will ship: NO

I have a very nice in nearly new condition parkerized Remington 870P Police Magnum. From the serial number on the barrel (LP) it appears that these guns were manufactured February 1995. Remington does cycles through their alphabet code approximately every 26 years, therefore there could be another possible date but with the low serial number on the receiver I think 1995 is the date, but please verify for yourself. This gun is all original and has not been modified in any way. 

Here are some differences between the Police and Express model:
• 870 Police shotguns go thru a special 23 station check list – ranging from visual inspection, functional testing, test firing, and final inspection.
• All Police shotguns are assembled in a “special build area” at the plant in Ilion, NY. This section is secured and serves only to build LE and Military shotguns, with the same factory personnel working at that assignment each shift.
• All parts that enter the “special build area” are visually inspected by hand to ensure top quality and functionality.
• Due to heavy recoil in buck and slug loads, all 870 Police guns have a longer
magazine spring which ensures positive feed and function.
• A heavier sear spring is used to generate a reliable, positive trigger pull between 5 and 8 lbs.
• A heavier carrier dog spring is used to ensure when the carrier elevates the shell, it will be held there until the bolt can push it into the chamber. This ensures positive feeding when using heavier payload rounds.
• Police shotguns do not have an ISS (Integrated Safety System) which is a locking mechanism on the safety of commercial shotguns. This type of locking mechanism can cause delay to an officer who needs the weapon but does not have the appropriate key. LE shotguns have the standard, proven, cross bolt safety.
• The fore-end on the Express model is longer and not compatible with many police shotgun vehicle racks.
• The Police shotguns utilize the heavy duty SPEEDFEED Stocks and Fore-ends.
• The Express model will not allow for the addition of an extension tube without physical modification to the tube and barrel, which can nullify the warranty.
• The Express model has a BEAD BLAST BLUE finish while the Police models utilize either High Luster bluing or Parkerization.
• The Express model utilizes a synthetic trigger housing while the Police models use a compressed metal housing.
• The Police shotgun barrel is locked down with a “ball detent” system in conjunction with the magazine cap vs. a lesser grade “synthetic magazine spring retainer” lock down as used on the Express system.
• The receivers used in Police guns are “vibra honed” to smooth out rough finishes and remove burrs before parkerization or bluing.
• Police shotguns use machined ejectors and extractors, as opposed to powdered metal cast which are utilized on the Express models.

title: For Sale:  REMINGTON 870 POLICE MAGNUM "TAGGED DEPT. OF CA CORRECTIONS
postcontent:
Make: Remington 

Model: 870P Police Magnum

Caliber: 12 Guage

Location: Sacramento 

Will ship: NO

I have a very nice in nearly new condition "State of California Corrections" Remington 870P Police Magnum. From the tag and the hand scribed "HDSP" on the receiver my guess is that this shotgun is from the High Dessert Security Prison. You don’t see a lot of LE trade ins that have an actual tag. It does not appear by the condition that this shotgun was used much if any. From the serial number on the barrel (KO and PO) it appears that these guns were manufactured May and June of 1977. Remington does cycles through their alphabet code approximately every 26 years, therefore March of 1994 could be another possible date but with the low serial number on the receiver I think 1977 is the date, but please verify for yourself. This gun is all original and has not been modified in any way. 

Here are some differences between the Police and Express model:
• 870 Police shotguns go thru a special 23 station check list – ranging from visual inspection, functional testing, test firing, and final inspection.
• All Police shotguns are assembled in a “special build area” at the plant in Ilion, NY. This section is secured and serves only to build LE and Military shotguns, with the same factory personnel working at that assignment each shift.
• All parts that enter the “special build area” are visually inspected by hand to ensure top quality and functionality.
• Due to heavy recoil in buck and slug loads, all 870 Police guns have a longer
magazine spring which ensures positive feed and function.
• A heavier sear spring is used to generate a reliable, positive trigger pull between 5 and 8 lbs.
• A heavier carrier dog spring is used to ensure when the carrier elevates the shell, it will be held there until the bolt can push it into the chamber. This ensures positive feeding when using heavier payload rounds.
• Police shotguns do not have an ISS (Integrated Safety System) which is a locking mechanism on the safety of commercial shotguns. This type of locking mechanism can cause delay to an officer who needs the weapon but does not have the appropriate key. LE shotguns have the standard, proven, cross bolt safety.
• The fore-end on the Express model is longer and not compatible with many police shotgun vehicle racks.
• The Police shotguns utilize the heavy duty SPEEDFEED Stocks and Fore-ends.
• The Express model will not allow for the addition of an extension tube without physical modification to the tube and barrel, which can nullify the warranty.
• The Express model has a BEAD BLAST BLUE finish while the Police models utilize either High Luster bluing or Parkerization.
• The Express model utilizes a synthetic trigger housing while the Police models use a compressed metal housing.
• The Police shotgun barrel is locked down with a “ball detent” system in conjunction with the magazine cap vs. a lesser grade “synthetic magazine spring retainer” lock down as used on the Express system.
• The receivers used in Police guns are “vibra honed” to smooth out rough finishes and remove burrs before parkerization or bluing.
• Police shotguns use machined ejectors and extractors, as opposed to powdered metal cast which are utilized on the Express models.

The RCS – which stands for 1911 Compact SAS – comes from the SIG SAUER® Customs Shop and has been put through the SIG Anti-Snag treatment which our gunsmiths developed to radically dehorn a pistol. Available in either a Natural Stainless (shown) or Nitron® finish the RCS comes with low profile night sights, checkered front strap (25-lpi), checkered mainspring housing (20-lpi) and slim profile custom wood grips. The grips are either gray diamondwood on the Stainless model or rosewood on the Nitron® version. Each of these 7+1 capacity RCS model 1911 pistols features a stainless steel slide, alloy frame, match grade barrel, hammer/sear set and trigger. The slides and frames are machined to exacting tolerances and hand-fitted to insure reliability.

Comes with boxes, papers, IWB, OWB holsters. 

5 magazines.

title: For Sale/Trade:  VERY RARE KIMBER SIS CUSTOM WITH MATCH GRADE THREADED BARREL
postcontent:
VERY GOOD COND HAS MATCH BARREL THREADED WITH IT 2 MAGS FACTORY CASE ALL ACC SLIGHT WEAR ON AMBI SAFETY HAS KIMBER NIGHT SITES 

The features of the new Kimber SIS have been selected with the job requirements of SIS and the training program of LAPD in mind. First, it is an ultra-reliable Kimber 1911 pistol. In .45 ACP, of course. Standard bushing and recoil-spring design–no full-length guide rods or bull barrels for the LAPD. The barrel is a Kimber match barrel, properly fitted to slide and frame. The trigger pull is clean and crisp, set in the five-pound region, and the solid trigger (aluminum, no extra holes) lacks an adjustable trigger stop.

The frame is checkered 30 lines to the inch, and the frame has the corners rounded. The sight is a specially modified Kimber fixed sight, with the front face squared off. The LAPD Academy teaches officers who need to do a one-handed slide cycle to do it by pressing the sight against their holster, duty belt or other convenient object. While members of the SIS do not work alone, and often use long arms, they specifically requested a rear sight that could be one-hand cycled.

Kimber, in laying out the pistol, figured a way to incorporate the “SIS” of the unit into the cocking serrations, If you look closely, you’ll see that the grooves are a stylized “SIS”.

On top of everything is the KimPro finish in dark gray over the stainless slide and frame. Why a baked-on finish on a high-end semi-custom gun? Well, Los Angeles is hot in the summer months. Sitting in plainclothes in their cars, it is a sure thing that officers will be sweating onto their sidearms, and no one wants a rusty blaster, now do they? It just doesn’t look right. And it might not work when you need it.
